[thinking] I'm considering how package-private classes are inaccessible through reflection if the class loader's runtime package differs. It’s tricky because, while the constructor can still be public, the class itself isn’t public, which might lead me to misunderstand the accessibility there. If I think about `getConstructor`, it looks like it might return public constructors, even for non-public classes. I should double-check the specifics about what `getConstructors` returns for public constructors. There's definitely some nuance here!
